# Add CAPTCHA Verification Step to Registration Flow

Add a server-side generated CAPTCHA challenge between email OTP verification and MFA authenticator setup.

**New registration flow:** Register → Email OTP → **CAPTCHA** → MFA Authenticator Setup

## Proposed Changes

### Backend
#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/server.js)
- Install `svg-captcha` package to generate CAPTCHA images server-side (no external API keys needed).
- Add `GET /api/captcha` — generates a random CAPTCHA, stores the answer in the user's session, and returns the SVG image.
- Add `POST /api/verify-captcha` — validates the user's answer against the session. On success, proceeds to generate the TOTP secret + QR code (moves this logic out of `/api/verify-email`).
- Modify `POST /api/verify-email` — on success, mark email as verified in `pendingUsers` but **don't** generate TOTP yet. Instead, respond with `{ success: true, requireCaptcha: true }`.

### Frontend
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/public/index.html)
- Add new `view-captcha` section between OTP and MFA setup views, containing a CAPTCHA image, text input, refresh button, and submit button.

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/public/js/app.js)
- After OTP verification succeeds → load CAPTCHA image and switch to `view-captcha`.
- On CAPTCHA submit → call `/api/verify-captcha`. On success, show MFA QR code setup.
- Add a "Refresh CAPTCHA" button handler to reload a new CAPTCHA image.

## Verification Plan
- Start the server and register a new user.
- After OTP verification, confirm the CAPTCHA view appears with an image.
- Verify wrong CAPTCHA answers show an error.
- Verify correct CAPTCHA answer proceeds to MFA setup with QR code.
